			<div class="content" id="post-content-2418917">
									

<p>I agree with the above sentiments. The body of the text could use some tightening. I laughed, though, so I upvoted.</p>
<p>Let's see what we can do&#8230;</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Object Class: SAFE for fuck's sake</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Gold. Keep this.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Special Containment Procedures: SCP-3V1L-J is to be kept in solitary confinement in a humanoid containment cell. No further communication is to be made between SCP-3V1L-J and staff.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I want to expand on that slightly. Like, make the frustration of speaking with him more clear. It's a bit lolfoundation by now, but I'd look over <a href="/scp-661">SCP-661</a> for ideas. No, let's not go into lists of smackdown, though.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>This pattern continued for some time. Primary containment of SCP-3V1L-J was established on 10/14/14.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Kind of feels truncated at this point. Perhaps a couple more hare-brained schemes building up to the ZK and greater Foundation response until they get it?</p>
<p>That interview, though, is just what it needs.</p>

